menu "Wake-on-LAN"

    config WOL_BROADCAST_PORT
        int "Magic Packet UDP port"
        default 9
        range 1 65535
        help
            UDP port the Magic Packet is sent to. Port 9 (discard) is the
            WoL standard and is what all PC BIOS/NIC implementations listen
            on by default. Only change this if your target PC's NIC or
            operating system requires a non-standard port.

    config WOL_BROADCAST_ADDR
        string "LAN broadcast address"
        default "192.168.1.255"
        help
            IPv4 broadcast address for the Magic Packet. This should be the
            directed broadcast of your home LAN subnet:

              192.168.1.x subnet  → 192.168.1.255
              192.168.0.x subnet  → 192.168.0.255
              10.0.0.x subnet     → 10.0.0.255

            The limited broadcast 255.255.255.255 also works on most routers
            but some firmware drops it. Use the directed broadcast for
            maximum compatibility.

            This value is set once at build time. If your LAN subnet does not
            match, rebuild with the correct address or change it via menuconfig.

endmenu
